m/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=453.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald changes</span><hr size=1> I believe that the Skald is a great class. I have a 50 skald and I have fun. However, with all the changes that have come up lately and with the new patch shaping up, what is the skalds purpose other than speed song?<br>
<br>
Damage song is weak and the range is a joke.<br>
Heal song is weak, enough said.<br>
DDs suck up alot of end usage and resists are off the charts.<br>
Mez and Snare just recieved another nerf not to include resisted more.<br>
Speed song is great, but has bugs.<br>
Resists are not effective. <br>
Our weaponskill is a joke, and we really dont do alot of melee damage anymore due to SC and resists being off the chart.<br>
<br>
With all of the additions into game, it is bringing the utility of the Skald down. A once balanced class is turning into a speedbot class quickly. Can we expect to see any changes to the class that will compensate? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vivaxkithicor>Vivax Kithicor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/15/03 7:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=453.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald changes</span><hr size=1> Yes, Mythic has promised horses!  Horses which can be ridden and driven by their player-owners.<br>
<br>
This may actually solve the skald problem by removing our last role.<br>
<br>
(And to those who predict horses will only be for PvE, then I guess only skalds needing exp will be obsolete.)<br>
<br>
